<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB0C0C38FFCFFF9E6BB0F8ECFE29F8FE" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6BB0F8ECFD60F89F" authority="Andre, 1881: 58" authorityName="Andre" authorityPageNumber="58" authorityYear="1881" box="[151,702,1825,1847]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmecocystus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="albicans" variety="livida">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6BB0F8ECFE4AF89F" box="[151,404,1825,1847]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Myrmecocystus albicans</emphasis>
var. 
<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFCFFF9E6AEBF8EFFD60F89F" box="[460,702,1825,1847]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6AEBF8EFFD90F89F" box="[460,590,1825,1847]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">livida André</emphasis>
, 1881: 58
</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Combination in 
<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFCFFF9E6851F8EFFAF3F89F" author="Wheeler, W. M. &amp; Mann, W. M." box="[886,1325,1825,1847]" page="173" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" year="1916">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6851F8EFFAF3F89F" authority=": Wheeler &amp; Mann, 1916: 173" authorityName="Wheeler &amp; Mann" authorityPageNumber="173" authorityYear="1916" box="[886,1325,1825,1847]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cataglyphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6851F8EFFC2EF89F" box="[886,1008,1825,1847]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Cataglyphis</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6F25F8EFFAF3F89F" author="Wheeler, W. M. &amp; Mann, W. M." box="[1026,1325,1825,1847]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="167 - 174" refId="ref9340" refString="Wheeler, W. M. &amp; Mann, W. M. (1916) The ants of the Phillips expedition to Palestine during 1914. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 60, 167 - 174." type="journal article" year="1916">Wheeler &amp; Mann, 1916:173</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. Raised to species: 
<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFCFFF9E6A3AF88EFE2DF8FE" author="Arnol'di, K. V." box="[285,499,1856,1878]" page="1810" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" year="1964">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6A3AF88EFE2DF8FE" author="Arnol'di, K. V." box="[285,499,1856,1878]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="1800 - 1815" refId="ref6133" refString="Arnol'di, K. V. (1964) Higher and specialized representatives of the ant genus Cataglyphis (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) in the fauna of the USSR. [In Russian.]. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 43, 1800 - 1815." type="journal article" year="1964">Arnol'di, 1964: 1810</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C306789DFFCFFF9D6BB0F84CFE90FF7D" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="571" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFCFFF9D6BB0F84CFE90FF7D" blockId="5.[151,1436,1922,2019]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="571" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
This species is widely distributed from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E697AF84DFD7EF833" box="[605,672,1923,1947]" name="Egypt" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Egypt</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E69EFF84CFC8FF833" box="[712,849,1922,1947]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6845F84CFBF5F833" author="Radchenko, A. G." box="[866,1067,1922,1947]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="424 - 442" refId="ref8032" refString="Radchenko, A. G. (1997) Review of ants of the genus Cataglyphis Foerster (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) of Asia. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 76, 424 - 442." type="journal article" year="1997">Radchenko, 1997</bibRefCitation>
) and has been reported from all countries of the Arabian Peninsula (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6915F868FCCEF817" author="Collingwood, C. A." box="[562,784,1958,1983]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="230 - 302" refId="ref6815" refString="Collingwood, C. A. (1985) Hymenoptera: Fam. Formicidae of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia, 7, 230 - 302." type="journal article" year="1985">Collingwood, 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6839F868FBAFF817" author="Tigar, B. J. &amp; Collingwood, C. A." box="[798,1137,1958,1983]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="13 - 14" refId="ref9012" refString="Tigar, B. J. &amp; Collingwood, C. A. (1993) A preliminary list of ant records from Abu Dhabi Emirate, UAE. Tribulus, 3, 13 - 14." type="journal article" year="1993">Tigar and Collingwood, 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6F59F868FF0DF84B" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D." pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="300 - 385" refId="ref6843" refString="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. (1996) Formicidae of Saudi Arabia (Part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 15, 300 - 385." type="journal article" year="1996">Collingwood and Agosti, 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6BC6F804FDDAF84B" author="Tigar, B. J. &amp; Osborne, P. E." box="[225,516,1994,2019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="171 - 182" refId="ref9049" refString="Tigar, B. J. &amp; Osborne, P. E. (1999) The influence of the lunar cycle on ground-dwelling invertebrates in an Arabian desert. Journal of Arid Environments, 43, 171 - 182. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1006 / jare. 1999.0541" type="journal article" year="1999">Tigar and Osborne, 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6935F804FCEEF84B" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. &amp; Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T." box="[530,816,1994,2019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="405 - 474" refId="ref6877" refString="Collingwood, C. A., Agosti, D., Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T. (2011) Order Hymenoptera, Family Formicidae. Arthropod Fauna of the UAE, 4, 405 - 474." type="journal article" year="2011">
Collingwood 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6988F805FD34F84B" box="[687,746,1994,2019]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6862F804FBC8F84B" baseAuthorityName="Andre" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[837,1046,1994,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cataglyphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="livida">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6862F804FBC8F84B" box="[837,1046,1994,2019]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Cataglyphis livida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common species at Rawdhat Khorim. Populations increase in spring and peak in June. This species was found abundantly foraging on 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCCFF9D6E69FF56FE90FF7D" authority="Benth." authorityName="Benth." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="571" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gerrardii">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCCFF9D6E69FF56FF22FF7D" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="571">Acacia gerrardii</emphasis>
Benth.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
